HEADWORD: Denigration
<hw>Den`i*gra"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>denigratio</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of making
black.</def> <rj><au>Boyle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fig.: A blackening; defamation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The vigorous <qex>denigration</qex> of science.</q>
<rj><qau>Morley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
